✅ Common Operations
1. Add a new column
ALTER TABLE table_name
ADD column_name datatype;

👉 Example:

ALTER TABLE students
ADD age INT;
2. Modify an existing column (datatype/size)
ALTER TABLE table_name
MODIFY column_name new_datatype;

👉 Example:

ALTER TABLE students
MODIFY age FLOAT;
3. Rename a column
ALTER TABLE table_name
RENAME COLUMN old_name TO new_name;

👉 Example:

ALTER TABLE students
RENAME COLUMN age TO student_age;
4. Delete a column
ALTER TABLE table_name
DROP COLUMN column_name;

👉 Example:

ALTER TABLE students
DROP COLUMN student_age;
5. Rename a table
ALTER TABLE old_table_name
RENAME TO new_table_name;

👉 Example:

ALTER TABLE students
RENAME TO student_details;
🎯 Simple Definition (Exam Ready)

👉 ALTER is used to change the structure of an existing table in a database.


