Other uses of alter

Good question 👍 — many students think ALTER is only for columns, but it has many more uses.

Here are other important uses of ALTER in SQL 👇

🔹 1. Add Constraints

You can add rules to a table after it is created.

ALTER TABLE students
ADD CONSTRAINT pk_student PRIMARY KEY (id);

👉 Used for:

PRIMARY KEY
FOREIGN KEY
UNIQUE
CHECK
🔹 2. Drop Constraints

Remove existing constraints.

ALTER TABLE students
DROP CONSTRAINT pk_student;
🔹 3. Add Default Value

Set a default value for a column.

ALTER TABLE students
ALTER COLUMN age SET DEFAULT 18;
🔹 4. Remove Default Value
ALTER TABLE students
ALTER COLUMN age DROP DEFAULT;
🔹 5. Change Column Name (Alternative syntax in some DBs)
ALTER TABLE students
CHANGE old_name new_name VARCHAR(50);

👉 (Used in MySQL)

🔹 6. Add / Drop Index
ALTER TABLE students
ADD INDEX idx_name (name);
ALTER TABLE students
DROP INDEX idx_name;
🔹 7. Rename Constraints
ALTER TABLE students
RENAME CONSTRAINT old_name TO new_name;
🔹 8. Change Table Properties

(Some DBMS allow storage or engine changes)

ALTER TABLE students
ENGINE = InnoDB;
🔹 9. Add Foreign Key
ALTER TABLE orders
ADD CONSTRAINT fk_customer
FOREIGN KEY (customer_id)
REFERENCES customers(id);